Sure, here are a few example sentences in Serbian that use the word "prirode" in different forms and positions:

1. *Priroda* je puna života u proleće. (*Nature* is full of life in spring.) 
2. Ova slika odražava lepotu *prirode*. (This picture reflects the beauty of *nature*.)
3. Moramo bolje brinuti o očuvanju *prirode*. (We need to take better care of *nature* conservation.)
4. *Prirodna* katastrofa je uzdrmala grad. (*Natural* disaster shook the city.)
5. *Prirodno* je da se plašimo mraka. (*It's natural* to be afraid of the dark.)
6. Vodim zdrav život i pazim na svoju *prirodu*. (I live a healthy lifestyle and take care of my *nature*.)
7. Planinarenje je odličan način da se povežete sa *prirodom*. (Hiking is a great way to connect with *nature*.)
8. *Prirodno* svetlo u sobi je mnogo bolje od veštačkog. (*Natural* light in a room is much better than artificial.)
9. *Priroda* se oporavlja nakon duge zime. (*Nature* is recovering after a long winter.)
10. Divim se lepoti *prirode* dok vozim bicikl. (I admire the beauty of *nature* while cycling.)

In each sentence, the word "priroda" (nature) is highlighted with an asterisk (*), and the English translations are provided in parentheses.